nodes.text: D'Lina was a female socialite who belonged to a bird-like species. She embarked on the maiden voyage of the luxury train Exas Jewell, which had been designed by her son Shen Kanton.
D'Lina appeared in "Off the Rails," a short comic written by Jeremy Barlow and illustrated by Bob Molesworth. Although her name does not appear in the story proper, it is mentioned in the script.
